    "body": "Tested the following scenarios:\r\n\r\n1. Open wallet > Add values for amount, To > Tap on Send\r\n2. Open wallet > Add values for amount, To > Tap on Cancel\r\n3. Open wallet > Add values for amount, To > Tap on Send > Sign with Keycard\r\n4. Open wallet > Add values for amount, To > Tap on Send > Cancel\r\n5. Open wallet > Add values for amount, To > Tap on Send > Sign with Keycard > Put card to the back of your phone for 1 sec > Processing screen\r\n![photo_2019-12-13 16 15 50](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/70810316-d81f9c80-1dc3-11ea-8624-1d3d1969a679.jpeg)\r\n- 5.1. If from this state you will tap on \"Cancel\", at attempt to sign transaction you will get endless spinner\r\n![photo_2019-12-13 16 32 06](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/70811569-22a21880-1dc6-11ea-8af2-40b267208b3a.jpeg)\r\n\r\nLogcat: \r\n[endless-processing.log](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/3961416/endless-processing.log)\r\nSo you are blocking in transaction signing until manual app restart.\r\n\r\n- 5.2. If wait for several mins and then put the card to NFC reader again, connection is not restored, so transaction signing stuck on endless processing.\r\nLogcat:\r\n[endl-processing-signing.log](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/3961457/endl-processing-signing.log)\r\n\r\nIssues 5.1. and 5.2. are reproducible from Dapp and from Wallet.\r\n@rasom let me know if I need to track 5.1 and 5.2  separately\r\n\r\n\r\n",
